(44, 9, 18, 47, 3, 14, 14, 'fell from his eyes as it had been scales', 'Spiritual Blindness and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual blindness and the subsequent revelation of truth. In Acts, the scales falling from Saul''s eyes symbolizes the removal of blindness, while in 2 Corinthians, the vail represents the ongoing spiritual blindness in understanding the Old Testament, which is removed in Christ.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
